## Early game

**Tessera** on Venus (Defense) is a short, low-level Corpus Defense on one of
Circuits' two signature planets, making it an easy repeat farm for a fresh
account. Circuits come from in-mission resource caches rather than an enemy
drop table, so Resource Drop Boosters and the Steel Path passive don't
increase them here — it's the number of caches found, not kills, that
matters.

## Mid & late game

**Gabii** on Ceres (Dark Sector Survival) is the wiki's higher-drop-rate
endgame pick, with Steel Path squads running it for longer per rotation than
a standard mission. Circuits are still cache-based rather than an enemy
drop, so the benefit of Steel Path here is simply a longer run with more
caches to loot, not a booster or drop-chance multiplier. Deploying a Titan
Extractor on Venus or Ceres is also a passive way to stock up Circuits
without actively farming.

